The article is a transcript of a conference call by senior administration officials on the situation in Iraq. The officials discussed the President's response to the crisis and the actions the US is taking to address the situation. They mentioned that the President has been meeting regularly with his national security team to monitor and review options for responding to the crisis. The officials discussed the priority of protecting US personnel in Iraq, supporting Iraq's stability and inclusive political process, and preventing the establishment of a safe haven for ISIS. They mentioned that the US has taken steps to secure its embassy in Iraq and has increased intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR) capabilities in the region. The US is also focused on building the capacity of Iraqi security forces and is sending additional military advisors to assist with training and support. The officials also discussed the possibility of US military action if necessary and the importance of diplomatic efforts to support an inclusive political process in Iraq.